# Lifecycle Marketing Automation Standards

## Lifecycle Mapping
- Define clear customer lifecycle stages from acquisition to advocacy
- Document transition criteria between lifecycle stages
- Create behavioral indicators for lifecycle stage identification
- Implement automated lifecycle stage assignment
- Apply consistent lifecycle terminology across systems
- Document lifecycle analytics and reporting requirements

## Stage-Specific Communication
- Create distinct communication strategies for each lifecycle stage
- Apply appropriate messaging tone for lifecycle position
- Implement content tailored to specific lifecycle needs
- Document communication frequency guidelines by lifecycle stage
- Create content libraries for each lifecycle stage
- Apply engagement scoring specific to lifecycle position

## Transition Management
- Implement automated detection of lifecycle transitions
- Create transition-triggered communication sequences
- Apply appropriate timing for transition acknowledgment
- Document successful transition indicators and metrics
- Implement recovery flows for negative transitions
- Create milestone celebrations for positive transitions

## Win-back and Retention
- Implement early warning systems for potential churn
- Create tiered intervention strategies based on churn risk
- Apply personalized win-back offers based on customer history
- Document effectiveness metrics for retention campaigns
- Implement post-win-back nurturing sequences
- Create long-term reactivation campaigns for dormant customers

## Customer Value Optimization
- Implement customer lifetime value forecasting
- Create value-based segmentation within lifecycle stages
- Apply investment strategies based on potential value
- Document value growth patterns across lifecycle
- Implement cross-sell and upsell automation appropriate to lifecycle stage
- Create loyalty and advocacy programs for high-value segments

